scripts.comment: One simple example using the block can be found below. This should return a list with 26 elements. It should start with 1, 2, 3 and then be filled with zeros!

Frequency analysis is a useful technique in cracking ciphers (especially monoalphabetic ciphers). This technique entails counting the letter frequencies and comparing them to the expected frequencies.
Edit the block on the left to view the problem!

block.l: Can you guess what shift value was used?
